If you're right, the test page should work in FF. You could try it.<p>Step 1 and 2 aren't required - the field names are 'standard'.<p>Step 3 is what the test page does already.<p>Edit: It looks like the javascript used to generate keypresses isn't supported by Firefox:<p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en/DOM/document.createEvent" rel="nofollow">https://developer.mozilla.org/en/DOM/document.createEvent</a><p><pre><code>    var event = document.createEvent('TextEvent');
    event.initTextEvent('textInput', true, true, null, char);

    input.value = "";
    input.selectionStart = 0;
    input.selectionEnd = 0;
    input.focus();
    input.dispatchEvent(event);</code></pre>
